Biomass chane at different levels of predation

Faith Jones

16 June 2017

Here i present the mixed model results for change in biomass of predators. There are three levels of predation: Wide (group 2 and 3 species), Middle (group2) and Narrow(Hoplias and Crenicichla). Only teh data from July/august is incuded so I could use the 2016 data. Also the survey eatken in 2010 is removed sure to sampling differences.

Narrow level predation definition

Here is the raw plot of predator biomass agaist time, and the plot of log2 biomass against time. There is a lot of variability.

BioPlot <- ggplot(FishDataTot, aes(x = Year, y = BiomassSum, col = site, group = site))
BioPlot + geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    theme_classic() +
    labs(title="The biomass of Hoplias and Crenicichla", y = "Predator Biomass (kg)")

BioPlotLog <- ggplot(FishDataTot, aes(x = Year, y = LogBiomass, col = site, group = site))
BioPlotLog + geom_point() +
    geom_line() +
    theme_classic() +
    labs(title="The log biomass of Hoplias and Crenicichla", y = "Log Predator Biomass (kg)")

Next is the mixed model results and plot of slopes of the sites

bioMLog <- lmer(LogBiomass ~ meanCentredYear + (meanCentredYear|site), data = FishDataTot)
summary(bioMLog)
## Linear mixed model fit by REML ['lmerMod']
## Formula: LogBiomass ~ meanCentredYear + (meanCentredYear | site)
##    Data: FishDataTot
## 
## REML criterion at convergence: 455.3
## 
## Scaled residuals: 
##      Min       1Q   Median       3Q      Max 
## -2.47947 -0.49056  0.00353  0.53203  2.57602 
## 
## Random effects:
##  Groups   Name            Variance Std.Dev. Corr 
##  site     (Intercept)     4.77104  2.1843        
##           meanCentredYear 0.02486  0.1577   -1.00
##  Residual                 4.89539  2.2126        
## Number of obs: 96, groups:  site, 16
## 
## Fixed effects:
##                 Estimate Std. Error t value
## (Intercept)      4.46117    0.59092   7.550
## meanCentredYear -0.07836    0.13798  -0.568
## 
## Correlation of Fixed Effects:
##             (Intr)
## meanCntrdYr -0.264
#plot slopes of sites
bioMLog_Lines <- coef(bioMLog )$site[c(1:2)] # get slope and intercept of each line in model 3
names(bioMLog_Lines) <- c("intercept", "slope")

m3.plotb <- ggplot(data = FishDataTot, aes(x = meanCentredYear, y = LogBiomass)) # plot of model with varying intercept but not slope, but only main slope shown
m3.plotb + geom_blank() + 
    theme_classic() + 
    geom_abline(slope =bioMLog_Lines$slope, intercept = bioMLog_Lines$intercept) +
    labs(title="The log biomass change of Hoplias and Crenicichla", y = "Log Predator Biomass (kg)")
